❌ Common Mistakes (VERY IMPORTANT)
❌ 1. Overthinking all splits

Trying:

for(i)
   check prefix == suffix

👉 Leads to TLE / wrong logic

❌ 2. Not realizing global AND

👉 Whole problem reduces to:

“How many elements equal to global AND?”

❌ 3. Using map unnecessarily
map<int,int> freq;

👉 Not needed, just count X

❌ 4. Computing factorial every test case

👉 Causes TLE

